{"_id":"post-fd7809e3-e100-411c-83ca-b5962bdae9bb","_type":"post","title":"Implementing RUI, Replit's Design System","slug":{"_type":"slug","current":"rui-eng"},"body":[{"_key":"eecd57a3498d","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"At Replit, we have a small engineering and design team supporting millions of users. Our secret is investing in good tools that make us more productive. In this blog post we'll give you an insider look into how we implemented one such tool - the Replit design system (or RUI for short).","_key":"eecd57a3498d0"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"132ea575e741","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"The project started as a collection of growth pains:","_key":"132ea575e7410"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"465a93107455","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Designers were stretched thin on multiple projects and they couldn't be involved in small tactical decisions","_key":"465a931074550"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal","level":1,"listItem":"number"},{"_key":"8af2aea715ee","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"UI was inconsistent across the product","_key":"8af2aea715ee0"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal","level":1,"listItem":"number"},{"_key":"89aa473c3ea6","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Reusing UI code was hard, so engineers built new ones (for example, we had 7 different Avatar components)","_key":"89aa473c3ea60"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal","level":1,"listItem":"number"},{"_key":"559c44b1057c","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"So, we set to build a design system that would help us scale. The high level goals:","_key":"559c44b1057c0"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"11456498333d","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Cover 90% of what we need (don't chase the very special cases)","_key":"11456498333d0"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal","level":1,"listItem":"number"},{"_key":"a1c462782472","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Easy, intuitive and fun to use","_key":"a1c4627824720"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal","level":1,"listItem":"number"},{"_key":"f91a6da84059","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Retain the full power of CSS when it's needed","_key":"f91a6da840590"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal","level":1,"listItem":"number"},{"_key":"40c0f3c8dbb9","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Technical path","_key":"40c0f3c8dbb90"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"h2"},{"_key":"523ba8c6a1eb","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Replit's frontend is built on top of React, a very popular library for building user interfaces. The React ecosystem has dozens of libraries and toolkits for making UIs. So many, that picking one is a hard problem!","_key":"523ba8c6a1eb0"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"e481d625746c","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Here's a list of libraries and approaches we have considered, and the pros and cons we weighed:","_key":"e481d625746c0"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"c1bfc8df25d6","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Styled JSX","_key":"c1bfc8df25d60"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"h3"},{"_key":"fb8eee916300","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":["code"],"text":"styled-jsx","_key":"fb8eee9163000"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" comes built-in with Next.js (which we also use), so most of Replit was styled with it.","_key":"fb8eee9163001"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_type":"codeBlock","language":"text","codeContent":"function AppsList(props) {\n  return (\n    <ul className=\"list\">\n      <AppComponent />\n      <style jsx>{`\n        .list {\n          color: ${props.cool ? 'blue' : 'black'}\n          padding: var(--spaceing-2);\n        }\n      `}</style>\n    </ul>\n  )\n}\n","_key":"70002f008bc2"},{"_key":"e926ab1df9da","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":["em"],"text":"Pros:","_key":"e926ab1df9da0"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"e73f2778cc6c","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Easy to hack together: there's nothing to import, just put the CSS next to your components.","_key":"e73f2778cc6c0"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal","level":1,"listItem":"number"},{"_key":"8c53043c06d7","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Class names communicate purpose (e.g. ","_key":"8c53043c06d70"},{"_type":"span","marks":["code"],"text":".section","_key":"8c53043c06d71"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":", ","_key":"8c53043c06d72"},{"_type":"span","marks":["code"],"text":".title","_key":"8c53043c06d73"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":")","_key":"8c53043c06d74"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal","level":1,"listItem":"number"},{"_key":"fa9d34532274","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Just copy-paste CSS from anywhere","_key":"fa9d345322740"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal","level":1,"listItem":"number"},{"_key":"62527b7743a5","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":["em"],"text":"Cons:","_key":"62527b7743a50"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"db565a242bcf","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Too easy to reinvent the wheel (which resulted in 7 different ","_key":"db565a242bcf0"},{"_type":"span","marks":["code"],"text":"<Avatar>","_key":"db565a242bcf1"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" component implementations)","_key":"db565a242bcf2"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal","level":1,"listItem":"number"},{"_key":"59983dfb63c4","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Composition is ","_key":"59983dfb63c40"},{"_type":"span","marks":["923871b4a523"],"text":"hard and confusing","_key":"59983dfb63c41"}],"markDefs":[{"_key":"923871b4a523","_type":"link","href":"https://replit.com/@frant1c/CssIsHard"}],"_type":"block","style":"normal","level":1,"listItem":"number"},{"_key":"fc92cb8d5b92","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"The defaults are not app-friendly (e.g. ","_key":"fc92cb8d5b920"},{"_type":"span","marks":["code"],"text":"box-sizing","_key":"fc92cb8d5b921"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":", ","_key":"fc92cb8d5b922"},{"_type":"span","marks":["code"],"text":"display: box","_key":"fc92cb8d5b923"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":")","_key":"fc92cb8d5b924"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal","level":1,"listItem":"number"},{"_key":"f71ac2845478","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Easy to have typos in CSS that can only be inspected visually (did you notice ","_key":"f71ac28454780"},{"_type":"span","marks":["code"],"text":"--spaceing-2","_key":"f71ac28454781"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" above?)","_key":"f71ac28454782"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal","level":1,"listItem":"number"},{"_key":"422d45bd2dbc","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Styled Components","_key":"422d45bd2dbc0"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"h3"},{"_key":"07fd00463840","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":["code"],"text":"styled-components","_key":"07fd004638400"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" was the first library that pioneered a \"styled\" API: making custom React components with CSS attached. Today, other libraries support a similar way of attaching CSS to components.","_key":"07fd004638401"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_type":"codeBlock","language":"text","codeContent":"const AppsList = styled.ul((props) => {\n  color: props.cool ? 'blue' : 'black',\n  padding: tokens.spacing2;\n});\n","_key":"237860f24f7b"},{"_key":"1c144ac2c385","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":["em"],"text":"Pros:","_key":"1c144ac2c3850"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"0e1e7fe3f33d","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Can use TypeScripted APIs (typecheck, IDE support)","_