:hover': {\n\n  },\n}}\n","_key":"b65351036858"},{"_key":"ad9a3b12eb1a","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":["em"],"text":"Pros","_key":"ad9a3b12eb1a0"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":": TypeScript, can do some pre-processing with code;\n","_key":"ad9a3b12eb1a1"},{"_type":"span","marks":["em"],"text":"Cons","_key":"ad9a3b12eb1a2"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":": hard to copy-paste, more keypresses to type out","_key":"ad9a3b12eb1a3"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"d0e38f353efe","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"RUI API","_key":"d0e38f353efe0"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"h1"},{"_key":"f8f08779a76e","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"In the end we landed on a system that's using Emotion with object-like styles, has a basic ","_key":"f8f08779a76e0"},{"_type":"span","marks":["code"],"text":"<View>","_key":"f8f08779a76e1"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" primitive, and provides tailwind-like utility traits that can be mixed in.","_key":"f8f08779a76e2"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"39d1a9308cd0","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Here's an example:","_key":"39d1a9308cd00"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_type":"codeBlock","language":"text","codeContent":"function AppsList(props) {\n  return (\n    <View tag=\"ul\" css={[\n      rcss.p(2), rcss.rowWithGap(1), \n      rcss.color.foregroundDimmer, \n      props.cool && rcss.color.accentPrimaryDimmer\n    ]}>\n      <AppComponent />\n    </View>\n  )\n}\n","_key":"17bf8c42d476"},{"_key":"ee7919e36c76","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":["code"],"text":"View","_key":"ee7919e36c760"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" is our basic building block. Inspired by React Native Web, it has a bunch of basic styles applied, e.g. ","_key":"ee7919e36c761"},{"_type":"span","marks":["code"],"text":"display: flex","_key":"ee7919e36c762"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":", ","_key":"ee7919e36c763"},{"_type":"span","marks":["code"],"text":"box-sizing: border-box","_key":"ee7919e36c764"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":", etc. ","_key":"ee7919e36c765"},{"_type":"span","marks":["code"],"text":"View","_key":"ee7919e36c766"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" accepts an optional ","_key":"ee7919e36c767"},{"_type":"span","marks":["code"],"text":"tag","_key":"ee7919e36c768"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" prop that makes sure the component is rendered as an appropriate semantic HTML element.","_key":"ee7919e36c769"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal","level":1,"listItem":"bullet"},{"_key":"66e8dc756c02","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"The ","_key":"66e8dc756c020"},{"_type":"span","marks":["code"],"text":"css","_key":"66e8dc756c021"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" prop is powered by Emotion. It accepts an object or an array of objects that contain CSS. Thanks to TypeScript support, we get a great IDE integration and safety guarantees (no more typos!)","_key":"66e8dc756c022"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal","level":1,"listItem":"bullet"},{"_key":"ad0128d58e65","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":["code"],"text":"rcss","_key":"ad0128d58e650"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" (stands for Replit CSS) is a set of utilities that are commonly used, like color, padding, alignment, etc.","_key":"ad0128d58e651"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal","level":1,"listItem":"bullet"},{"_key":"1d90def214d4","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"The utilities are super useful and have replaced most of our old \"layout components\". For example, we have a utility called ","_key":"1d90def214d40"},{"_type":"span","marks":["code"],"text":"rcss.rowWithGap","_key":"1d90def214d41"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" that aligns children components in a row with a gap between them. In the past, we used a special ","_key":"1d90def214d42"},{"_type":"span","marks":["code"],"text":"<VStack>","_key":"1d90def214d43"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" component for that. Using the utility is much nicer because it can be mixed into component style without making the React tree more complex.","_key":"1d90def214d44"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"0c5afc50d518","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Here's another example. As you can see below, we can \"mix-in\" a bunch of shared styles (like interactive list item), and Emotion makes sure we can override bits we want to customize:","_key":"0c5afc50d5180"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_type":"codeBlock","language":"text","codeContent":"function Button({ big, caption, className }) {\n  return (\n    <View\n      tag=\"button\"\n      css={[\n        buttonReset,\n        interactive.listItem,\n        rcss.p(big ? 8 : 4),\n        rcss.borderRadius(8),\n        { alignSelf: 'start' },\n      ]}\n      className={className}\n    >\n      {caption}\n    </View>\n  );\n}\n","_key":"f90f648afc3c"},{"_key":"0213d5f2ca5a","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"If needed, the new ","_key":"0213d5f2ca5a0"},{"_type":"span","marks":["code"],"text":"<Button>","_key":"0213d5f2ca5a1"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" can also be styled with ","_key":"0213d5f2ca5a2"},{"_type":"span","marks":["code"],"text":"css","_key":"0213d5f2ca5a3"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" prop: ","_key":"0213d5f2ca5a4"},{"_type":"span","marks":["code"],"text":"<Button css={{color: red}} />","_key":"0213d5f2ca5a5"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" (that's why we need to pipe ","_key":"0213d5f2ca5a6"},{"_type":"span","marks":["code"],"text":"className","_key":"0213d5f2ca5a7"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" — Emotion is a little unintuitive here).","_key":"0213d5f2ca5a8"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"13ec62009a09","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Our experience so far","_key":"13ec62009a090"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"h2"},{"_key":"81b5c9204932","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"It's been ~ 4 months since we started using RUI and our experience has mainly been very positive. Engineers love the new system and feel productive from day one.","_key":"81b5c92049320"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"5427493d4bb5","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"The IDE support means that the APIs are discoverable and type-safe, so we have more confidence than ever shipping new code.","_key":"5427493d4bb50"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"723db9e089ce","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Alongside the design system we've also built an internal page that has component examples and documentation (generated from source code).","_key":"723db9e089ce0"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"56e72ad98e33","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"56e72ad98e330","text":"","marks":[]}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"41218357f397","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"All our new code is written using RUI, and we opportunistically upgrade the old ","_key":"41218357f3970"},{"_type":"span","marks":["code"],"text":"<styled jsx>","_key":"41218357f3971"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":", which results in much less code.","_key":"41218357f3972"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"ad12dfef2788","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Acknowledgements","_key":"ad12dfef27880"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"h2"},{"_key":"356172a2885b","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Big props to Ashlynn for brainstorming the API and implementation ideas and Barron for setting the design system principles principles and being a kick-ass designer-who-codes.","_key":"356172a2885b0"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"4e27de9451d2","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"We expect that real success will only be achieved through close collaboration between system-sensitized visual and conceptual designers and design-centered software engineers and managers.\n— Designing Visual Interfaces, 1995, Sun Microsystems","_key":"4e27de9451d20"}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"blockquote"}],"publishedAt":"2021-12-23T00:00:00.000Z"}